<P>GALATEA, A PASTORAL ROMANCE; IMITATED FROM CERVANTES, BY M. DE FLORIAN. TRANSLATED INTO ENGLISH. TO WHICH IS ADDED, AMELIA, OR THE FAITHLESS BRITON; AMELIA, OR MALEVOLENCE DEFEATED; AND, MISS SEWARD'S MONODY ON MAJOR ANDRE. EMBELLISHED WITH ENGRAVINGS.</P>
<P>BOSTON: PRINTED FOR AND SOLD BY W. SPOTSWOOD, AND C. P. WAYNE. 1798.</P>
</DIV1>
